So, which of my boys is in trouble?

382
00:16:23,544 --> 00:16:25,244
暂时还不确定
Well, not sure any are yet.

383
00:16:25,246 --> 00:16:26,645
所以我们才来到这儿
That's why we're here.

384
00:16:26,647 --> 00:16:29,348
希望得到协助
Hoping for an assist.

385
00:16:29,350 --> 00:16:31,917
我们想和一个学员谈一谈 Terrence Lewis
We'd like to talk with one of your cadets, Terrence Lewis.

386
00:16:31,919 --> 00:16:34,253
我也想
Well, so would I.

387
00:16:34,255 --> 00:16:36,789
Lewis士兵已经擅自缺勤三周了
Private Lewis has been UA for three weeks now.

388
00:16:36,791 --> 00:16:39,525
但我说不上这不正常
Wish I could say that was unusual.

389
00:16:39,527 --> 00:16:41,260
Lewis经常失踪吗
Lewis go missing often?

390
00:16:41,262 --> 00:16:43,295
很遗憾 是的
Unfortunately, yes.

391
00:16:45,333 --> 00:16:47,766
我们很自豪能在这里改造孩子
We take pride here in reforming boys,

392
00:16:47,768 --> 00:16:49,468
教他们遵守规矩
teaching 'em to obey orders,

393
00:16:49,470 --> 00:16:52,838
如何面对比自身强大的东西
how to commit to something larger than themselves.

394
00:16:52,840 --> 00:16:54,707
但是 我们并不总能成功
But, we're not always successful

395
00:16:54,709 --> 00:16:56,242
恐怕Lewis士兵就是这一类
and I'm afraid that includes Private Lewis.

396
00:16:56,244 --> 00:16:58,344
你通知警局他失踪了吗
You notify NOPD he was missing?

397
00:16:58,346 --> 00:16:59,411
他们人手不足
They don't have the manpower

398
00:16:59,413 --> 00:17:01,714
无法追踪逃跑者 而且...
to chase down runaways and...

399
00:17:01,716 --> 00:17:04,483
像Lewis这样的孩子没有优先级
juvies like Lewis aren't a high priority.

400
00:17:04,485 --> 00:17:06,018
他做了什么
What's he done?

401
00:17:06,020 --> 00:17:08,954
重申一遍 我们不确定 但是
Again, not sure, but, uh...

402
00:17:11,993 --> 00:17:13,926
很抱歉这么说
I'm sorry to say,

403
00:17:13,928 --> 00:17:16,862
Noah Sandler律师被杀害了
JAG Noah Sandler has been murdered.

404
00:17:18,299 --> 00:17:21,167
Terrence Lewis是嫌犯之一
And Terrence Lewis is a person of interest.

405
00:17:22,270 --> 00:17:25,804
Noah 天啊
Noah, my God.

406
00:17:25,806 --> 00:17:27,673
怎么回事 什么时候
How, when?

407
00:17:27,675 --> 00:17:29,608
昨晚
Last night.

408
00:17:29,610 --> 00:17:33,546
我们现在知道的是 Noah在调查Lewis
And what we know now is: Noah was investigating Lewis.

409
00:17:33,548 --> 00:17:35,414
也许还调查这个学校
And maybe even the academy.

410
00:17:35,416 --> 00:17:36,949
调查
Investigating?

411
00:17:36,951 --> 00:17:38,851
Noah从来没和我说过
Noah never said anything to me about it

412
00:17:38,853 --> 00:17:40,953
他一直在这里
and he was here all the time.

413
00:17:40,955 --> 00:17:43,856
他教导许多孩子 不只有Lewis士兵
He mentored lots of boys, not just Private Lewis.

414
00:17:43,858 --> 00:17:46,258
我们可以和Lewis的指挥官谈一谈吗
Is it all right if we speak with Lewis' commanding officer?

415
00:17:46,260 --> 00:17:48,694
当然
Of course. Uh...

416
00:17:48,696 --> 00:17:52,031
Dorsey 请进来
Dorsey, come in here, please.

417
00:17:54,735 --> 00:17:56,368
长官
Sir?

418
00:17:56,370 --> 00:17:58,971
这些是NCIS的探员们 Dorsey上校
These are NCIS agents, Captain Dorsey.

419
00:17:58,973 --> 00:18:00,673
他们要和Carbral少校谈话 越快越好
They need to speak to Commander Cabral ASAP.

420
00:18:00,675 --> 00:18:02,942
好的 长官 这边请
Yes, sir. Right this way.

421
00:18:04,679 --> 00:18:06,812
Pride探员
Agent Pride?

422
00:18:06,814 --> 00:18:10,649
Noah去世的消息会严重打击到孩子们
This news of Noah's death is gonna hit the boys hard.

423
00:18:10,651 --> 00:18:13,352
我希望由我来告诉他们 如果可以的话
I'd rather they hear it from me, if that's all right with you.

424
00:18:13,354 --> 00:18:15,221
好的
Yes, sir.

425
00:18:25,099 --> 00:18:26,899
有什么发现 Loretta
What do we got, Loretta?

426
00:18:28,069 --> 00:18:29,868
抱歉 这个问法太像Pride了
I'm sorry, that was way too much like Pride.

427
00:18:29,870 --> 00:18:31,804
那太糟糕了 我得改一改
That was awful. God, I got to work on that.

428
00:18:31,806 --> 00:18:33,472
我会改的 会好的
I'll work on it, it's gonna be fine.

429
00:18:33,474 --> 00:18:36,742
别用力过猛 Sebastian 你做得不错
Stop trying so hard, Sebastian, you're doing fine.

430
00:18:36,744 --> 00:18:38,677
我知道 我知道 我知道 只是
I know, I know, I know, it's just...

431
00:18:38,679 --> 00:18:42,381
我大概还在找自己在NCIS的风格
still trying to find my NCIS way, I guess. You know?

432
00:18:42,383 --> 00:18:44,116
也许我应该继续做个闷罐子
Maybe I should keep the moped.

433
00:18:44,118 --> 00:18:45,851
你是来问进展的吧
You here for an update?

434
00:18:45,853 --> 00:18:47,753
没错 好几颗求知的心想要知道进展
I am. Yeah, inquiring minds want to know.

435
00:18:47,755 --> 00:18:49,255
尤其是Pride
Especially Pride's.

436
00:18:49,257 --> 00:18:51,924
显然 一个完整的尸体会有帮助
Well, obviously, an intact body would have helped,

437
00:18:51,926 --> 00:18:54,927
但是从可见的割伤和磨损的痕迹
but from the pattern of the cuts and abrasions I've seen,

438
00:18:54,929 --> 00:18:57,496
以及没有凝血作用来看
coupled with the lack of coagulation,

439
00:18:57,498 --> 00:19:01,800
Noah律师的尸体是在死后被拖过去的
it appears JAG Noah's body was dragged postmortem.

440
00:19:01,802 --> 00:19:03,602
因为嘀嗒嘀嗒的鳄鱼么
Because of Tick-Tock Croc?

441
00:19:04,372 --> 00:19:06,939
这是《彼得潘》里面的
It's a <i>Peter Pan</i> reference.

442
00:19:06,941 --> 00:19:08,474
不管怎么说
Anyway,

443
00:19:08,476 --> 00:19:10,109
短吻鳄的咬痕
the alligator bite pattern didn't match

444
00:19:10,111 --> 00:19:13,379
跟割痕的方向并不一致 所以
the indicated direction of the cuts, so...

445
00:19:13,381 --> 00:19:15,881
凶手一定是射杀Noah以后 才把他拖走的
So the killer must have dragged Noah after he shot him,

446
00:19:15,883 --> 00:19:17,416
拖到离水更近的地方
closer to the water.

447
00:19:17,418 --> 00:19:20,552
指望着短吻鳄能吃掉证据
Hoping the alligators would devour the evidence, yes.

448
00:19:20,554 --> 00:19:22,488
不过对我们确认凶手身份
Doesn't really get us any closer

449
00:19:22,490 --> 00:19:24,990
没什么很大的帮助
to IDing the killer, though.

450
00:19:24,992 --> 00:19:26,625
我们有没有什么办法
Is there any way that we can, uh,

451
00:19:26,627 --> 00:19:28,327
能缩小枪支范围的
narrow down what type of gun was used?

452
00:19:28,329 --> 00:19:30,663
这肯定是某种自动步枪
It was definitely an automatic rifle of some kind.

453
00:19:30,665 --> 00:19:32,498
根据
Based on the...

454
00:19:32,500 --> 00:19:34,667
入射伤口来看 可能是军用枪支
entry wound, probably military.

455
00:19:34,669 --> 00:19:37,336
在你找到子弹之前 我没法确定
I can't be sure until you find me the projectiles.

456
00:19:37,338 --> 00:19:39,138
是啊 这就得看运气了 对吧
Yeah, well, good luck with that, right?

457
00:19:39,140 --> 00:19:41,940
一个威力强大的步枪 子弹穿过人体
A high-powered rifle, bullets went right through the body,

458
00:19:41,942 --> 00:19:44,209
可能被埋在小河附近的什么地方
it's probably buried back in the bayou somewhere.

459
00:19:44,211 --> 00:19:45,804
嗯 在我听来像是需要一次外勤行动
Mm-hmm. Sounds like a field trip to me.

460
00:19:45,828 --> 00:19:47,346
没错
Yeah.

461
00:19:47,848 --> 00:19:49,315
等等 你是说我吗
Wait, do you mean me?

462
00:19:51,752 --> 00:19:53,085
你想让我回到那个
You-- you want me to go back out there

463
00:19:53,087 --> 00:19:55,521
致命的短吻鳄的世界 我一个人
to deadly gator-world? By myself?

464
00:19:55,523 --> 00:19:57,956
嘀嗒嘀嗒的鳄鱼
Tick-Tock Croc.

465
00:20:01,595 --> 00:20:03,295
好吧
All right.

466
00:20:03,297 --> 00:20:04,963
我不会再见到你了
I'll see you never.

467
00:20:06,767 --> 00:20:08,067
全体注意 立正
<i>Platoon, atten-hut!</i>

468
00:20:08,069 --> 00:20:09,568
下午好 长官
Good afternoon, sir.

469
00:20:09,570 --> 00:20:10,936
稍息 少校
At ease, Commander.

470
00:20:10,938 --> 00:20:13,138
Cabral少校 这些是NCIS探员
Commander Cabral, these are NCIS agents.

471
00:20:13,140 --> 00:20:14,973
他们需要跟你单独说几句话
They need to speak with you in private.

472
00:20:14,975 --> 00:20:17,643
好的 长官
Of course, sir.

473
00:20:17,645 --> 00:20:19,311
Cole 出列
Cole, front and center.

474
00:20:21,816 --> 00:20:23,749
你来指挥 上尉
Your command, Lieutenant.

475
00:20:23,751 --> 00:20:25,651
是 长官
Aye, sir.

476
00:20:28,322 --> 00:20:30,089
我还是不能理解
Still can't wrap my head around

477
00:20:30,091 --> 00:20:32,291
教少年犯用M16步枪射击
how teaching juvies to shoot M16s

478
00:20:32,293 --> 00:20:34,059
跟改造他们有什么关系
helps reform them.

479
00:20:34,061 --> 00:20:36,495
这不在于怎么射击 而在于教导他们什么是责任
Well, it's not about that. It teaches them responsibility.

480
00:20:36,497 --> 00:20:38,564
至少这里给了他们一个机会
At least this place gives them a chance.

481
00:20:38,566 --> 00:20:40,165
举枪
Port arms!

482
00:20:41,902 --> 00:20:43,335
我能怎么协助你们
How can I be of assistance?

483
00:20:43,337 --> 00:20:44,937
我知道Terrence Lewis
I understand Terrence Lewis

484
00:20:44,939 --> 00:20:46,705
曾经在你的小队里 少校
was in your squad, Commander?

485
00:20:46,707 --> 00:20:49,241
依然在我的小队里 是的
<i>Is</i> in my squad. Yes, sir.

486
00:20:49,243 --> 00:20:50,976
不过 列兵Lewis近来...
Although, currently, Private Lewis is...

487
00:20:50,978 --> 00:20:53,145
失踪了 我知道 你跟他熟吗
UA, I know. How well do you know him?

488
00:20:53,147 --> 00:20:56,515
Walsh上将三个月前把他分配到我的小队里
General Walsh assigned him to my squad three months ago.

489
00:20:56,517 --> 00:20:58,650
希望我能帮他改邪归正
Hoped I could straighten him out.

490
00:20:58,652 --> 00:21:01,687
-怎么个情况 -能自由发言吗
- How so? - Permission to speak freely?

491
00:21:01,689 --> 00:21:04,256
我们只是想寻找答案
We're just looking for answers.

492
00:21:04,258 --> 00:21:05,724
只要有帮助 说什么都行
However you can help.

493
00:21:07,962 --> 00:21:09,862
列兵Lewis是新兵中的刺头
Private Lewis was a difficult recruit.

494
00:21:09,864 --> 00:21:11,997
这个学校
The academy prides itself

495
00:21:11,999 --> 00:21:15,868
以忠诚和服从命令为荣
on strength through loyalty, following orders.

496
00:21:15,870 --> 00:21:18,103
Lewis完全反着来
Lewis fought it every step of the way.

497
00:21:18,105 --> 00:21:20,839
所以我可以理解为 你跟Lewis相处得并不好
So I take it you and Lewis didn't get along very well.

498
00:21:20,841 --> 00:21:23,542
Lewis跟谁相处得都不好
Lewis didn't get along with anyone very well.

499
00:21:23,544 --> 00:21:26,712
-那Noah律师呢 -律师
- What about JAG Noah? - JAG...

500
00:21:26,714 --> 00:21:29,615
他是最好的 他一直在我们身边
He's the best, he's always been there for us.

501
00:21:29,617 --> 00:21:32,284
他也帮Lewis 但是
Lewis, too, but...

502
00:21:32,286 --> 00:21:33,786
但是什么 孩子
But what, son?

503
00:21:36,357 --> 00:21:38,757
就在几周前 Noah律师想帮他
Just a few weeks ago, JAG Noah tried to help Lewis

504
00:21:38,759 --> 00:21:40,726
从一些麻烦中脱身
with some stuff he was going through.

505
00:21:40,728 --> 00:21:43,195
但是Lewis发了飚
But Lewis got mad.

506
00:21:43,197 --> 00:21:44,797
变得更暴力
Violent, even.

507
00:21:44,799 --> 00:21:47,232
还狠狠地打了Noah律师
Hit JAG Noah-- hard, too.

508
00:21:48,502 --> 00:21:50,736
之后再也没人见过他
That's the last anyone ever saw of him.

509
00:21:56,177 --> 00:21:58,010
那是什
What the...?

510
00:22:20,234 --> 00:22:22,134
找到了
Bingo.

511
00:22:37,117 --> 00:22:38,484
好的
Okay.

512
00:22:54,668 --> 00:22:56,034
哦 天呐
Oh, my God!

513
00:23:08,660 --> 00:23:10,726
根据腐烂程度
Judging by the rate of decomposition,

514
00:23:10,728 --> 00:23:13,362
我推测这个男孩大概死于三周前
I'd estimate the boy died about three weeks ago.

515
00:23:13,364 --> 00:23:15,364
跟Lewis失踪的时间一致
Same time Lewis went UA.

516
00:23:15,366 --> 00:23:16,365
死因呢
Cause of death?

517
00:23:16,367 --> 00:23:17,366
你这位失踪的学员
Your missing cadet

518
00:23:17,368 --> 00:23:18,834
明显被打过
was obviously beaten.

519
00:23:18,836 --> 00:23:20,736
即使过了这么久 他脸上
Even after all this time, bruises on his face,

520
00:23:20,738 --> 00:23:22,505
胳膊上和胸口的伤痕依然明显
arms, and chest are still evident.

521
00:23:22,507 --> 00:23:24,840
是啊 但更有意思的是 打他的凶器是什么
Yeah, more interesting, though, is what was used to beat him.

522
00:23:24,842 --> 00:23:26,542
我们复原了
Yes, we recovered the same substance

523
00:23:26,544 --> 00:23:29,145
表皮淤伤里发现的物质
found in the epidermis of the bruises--

524
00:23:29,147 --> 00:23:31,948
碱液 甘油 氢氧化钾
lye, glycerin, potassium hydroxide...

525
00:23:31,950 --> 00:23:35,017
也就是肥皂 我们甚至在他的嘴里发现了大量的肥皂痕迹
I.e., soap. We even found trace amounts of it in Lewis' mouth.

526
00:23:35,019 --> 00:23:37,186
-肥皂 -肥皂打人
- Soap? - Soap bashing.

527
00:23:37,188 --> 00:23:41,023
是军队一直谴责的一种欺凌方式
A hazing technique the military has long condemned.

528
00:23:41,025 --> 00:23:44,026
只不过肥皂不能打断这个男孩的顶骨
Except soap didn't break the boy's parietal bone.

529
00:23:44,028 --> 00:23:45,661
死因是后脑上
The cause of death was a sharp blow

530
00:23:45,663 --> 00:23:47,430
致命的一击 我还在试着
to the back of the head, and I'm still trying

531
00:23:47,432 --> 00:23:49,398
查清具体用的是什么凶器
to figure out exactly what was used.

532
00:23:49,400 --> 00:23:51,100
欺凌过头了吗
Hazing gone too far?

533
00:23:51,102 --> 00:23:53,803
如果是这样 Noah律师是把Lewis当成受害者
If so, JAG Noah may have been investigating

534
00:23:53,805 --> 00:23:56,505
而不是少年犯来进行调查
Terrence Lewis as a victim, not a juvie.

535
00:23:56,507 --> 00:23:58,474
不知怎么查出了弃尸地点
Somehow figured out where the body had been dumped,

536
00:23:58,476 --> 00:24:00,476
前往Verre湖边调查
went to Lake Verret to investigate,

537
00:24:00,478 --> 00:24:02,445
然后被杀害Lewis的人射杀了
and then got shot by whoever killed Lewis.

538
00:24:02,447 --> 00:24:05,948
我真不想这么说 但是如果不止一个学员
Well, I hate to say it, but if more than one cadet

539
00:24:05,950 --> 00:24:08,618
羞辱过Lewis 那很难相信
really did haze Lewis, then it's hard to believe

540
00:24:08,620 --> 00:24:10,653
他们与两起谋杀案没有关联
they're not responsible for both murders.

541
00:24:10,655 --> 00:24:12,688
我们不能直接下结论 好吗
We're not gonna jump to conclusions here, okay?

542
00:24:12,690 --> 00:24:14,123
我们需要确认
We need to be sure.

543
00:24:14,125 --> 00:24:18,260
好了 Loretta 我需要准确知道
Okay, Loretta, I need to know what <i>exactly</i>

544
00:24:18,262 --> 00:24:20,062
杀害Terrence Lewis的凶器
was used to kill Terrence Lewis.

545
00:24:20,064 --> 00:24:21,130
马上去
On it.

546
00:24:21,132 --> 00:24:22,198
Sebastian
Sebastian,

547
00:24:22,200 --> 00:24:23,299
查清杀害Noah律师的子弹
get an ID on those bullets

548
00:24:23,301 --> 00:24:24,333
都是什么型号
that killed JAG Noah.

549
00:24:24,335 --> 00:24:25,601
我想尽快知道
I want to know what type of weapon

550
00:24:25,603 --> 00:24:26,769
它们来自哪种武器
they came from ASAP.

551
00:24:26,771 --> 00:24:28,571
-收到 -你要去哪
- Copy that. - Where you going?

552
00:24:28,573 --> 00:24:29,739
Rita刚发了信息
Rita just texted.

553
00:24:29,741 --> 00:24:31,140
我得试着拖延她
I need to try and slow her down.

554
00:24:31,142 --> 00:24:33,509
她一到就让她上来
Send her up as soon as she gets here.

555
00:24:36,881 --> 00:24:39,515
Max Cabral 用致命武器袭击
Max Cabral, assault with a deadly weapon.

556
00:24:39,517 --> 00:24:41,550
William Cole 暴力袭击
William Cole, aggravated assault.

557
00:24:41,552 --> 00:24:43,753
-Jamal Povey 强奸未遂 -Rita
- Jamal Povey, attempted rape. - Rita...

558
00:24:43,755 --> 00:24:46,689
Tyler Wilson 持枪抢劫 名单还没完呢
Tyler Wilson, armed robbery. And the list goes on.

559
00:24:46,691 --> 00:24:48,991
在听到发生什么之后
I unsealed every cadet's criminal record

